      <div class="content-section"><div class="section-header"><span class="section-tag">Overview</span><h2>What Are Small Cap Funds?</h2></div>
        <p>Small cap mutual funds invest a minimum of 65% of their assets in stocks of companies ranked beyond 250th by market capitalization, as defined by SEBI. These companies typically have market caps below ₹15,000 crore and include emerging businesses, niche market leaders, regional champions, and companies in their early growth phases.</p>
        <p>The small cap universe in India comprises over 4,000+ listed companies across diverse sectors — from specialty manufacturing and regional banking to emerging technology and healthcare. While individual small cap stocks carry significant risk, a well-managed small cap fund diversifies across 50–80 such companies, mitigating single-stock risk while retaining the high growth potential.</p>
        <p>Historically, small cap funds have been the top-performing equity category over 10+ year periods, delivering 18%–25% CAGR. However, they are also the most volatile — small caps fell 40%–55% during the 2020 crash. This extreme volatility requires iron discipline: invest only money you won't need for 7+ years and maintain SIPs through market cycles.</p>
      </div>

