      <div class="content-section"><div class="section-header"><span class="section-tag">Benefits</span><h2>Why Invest in Small Cap Funds?</h2></div>
        <ul class="feature-list">
          <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>Highest Return Potential</strong><p>Small caps have delivered 18%–25% CAGR over 10-year periods — the highest among all equity categories. ₹10,000 monthly SIP at 22% CAGR for 15 years would grow to approximately ₹1.15 crore (₹18 lakh invested), demonstrating the power of compounding in high-growth assets.</p></div></li>
          <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>Multi-Bagger Opportunities</strong><p>Today's small caps can be tomorrow's large caps. Companies like Astral Pipes, Deepak Nitrite, and Dixon Technologies were small caps a decade ago and delivered 10x–50x returns. Small cap funds give you exposure to such potential multi-baggers through professional stock selection.</p></div></li>
          <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>Access Untapped Growth Sectors</strong><p>Many emerging sectors — electric vehicles, green energy, specialty chemicals, digital infrastructure — are dominated by small cap companies. These funds provide exposure to India's next-generation growth stories before they become mainstream.</p></div></li>
          <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>Professional Stock Selection</strong><p>With 4,000+ small cap stocks, individual stock picking is extremely risky. Fund managers use deep research, management meetings, and rigorous screening to identify the best 50–80 companies, reducing the risk of picking duds.</p></div></li>
          <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>SIP Maximizes Returns in Volatility</strong><p>Small cap volatility is actually an advantage for SIP investors. When small caps crash 40%–50%, your SIP buys significantly more units at depressed prices. When markets recover, these extra units compound to generate outsized returns.</p></div></li>
          <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>Portfolio Alpha Generator</strong><p>Even a 10%–15% allocation to small caps can meaningfully boost overall portfolio returns. As a satellite holding alongside large cap core, small caps add growth alpha that helps your portfolio significantly outperform inflation over decades.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="content-section"><div class="section-header"><span class="section-tag">How to Invest</span><h2>How to Invest in Small Cap Funds</h2></div>
        <div class="steps-grid">
          <div class="step-card"><div class="step-num">1</div><h3>Confirm Your Risk Appetite</h3><p>Small caps can fall 50%+ in bear markets. Only invest money you absolutely won't need for 7–10 years. Ensure you have large cap and emergency funds in place before adding small cap exposure.</p></div>
          <div class="step-card"><div class="step-num">2</div><h3>Limit Allocation to 10%–20%</h3><p>Keep small cap allocation at 10%–20% of your total equity portfolio. This provides meaningful upside while limiting drawdown impact on your overall wealth during market crashes.</p></div>
          <div class="step-card"><div class="step-num">3</div><h3>Always Use SIP Route</h3><p>Never invest lump sum in small caps. SIP is mandatory to manage the extreme volatility. Start with ₹2,000–₹5,000/month and stay disciplined through both bull and bear markets.</p></div>
          <div class="step-card"><div class="step-num">4</div><h3>Stay for 7+ Years Minimum</h3><p>Small cap fund returns become consistent only over 7+ year periods. Short-term returns can be wildly unpredictable. Set it, forget it, and let compounding work its magic over a full market cycle.</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
